<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-819-884  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 819 884.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  Sept 1990 v15 n9 p276(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>On BASIC.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kemeny, John; Kurtz, Thomas.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The BASIC programming language got off to a bad start in themicrocomputer field, with extremely poor versions of the languagecrammed onto tiny machines.andP;  As a result, many people got a false,negative impression of BASIC.andP;  Good, structured BASIC is actuallya good language to program in.andP;  The future of BASIC may well be asthe language of choice for people doing FORTRAN-type programmingbut wanting a language with an easier interface.andP;  Eventually amore modern version of BASIC will develop, but the transition willbe an extremely slow one.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Programming LanguagesBASICFuture of Computing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>